.TH AUDIOCONTROL_SCAN_LIBRARY 1 "July 2025" "audiocontrol" "Audio Control Manual"
.SH NAME
audiocontrol_scan_library \- scan and update music library from MPD or LMS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B audiocontrol_scan_library
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B audiocontrol_scan_library
is a command-line tool for scanning and updating music libraries from MPD (Music Player Daemon) or LMS (Lyrion Music Server). It performs a full library refresh and optionally displays statistics about the loaded library including album count, artist count, and total tracks.
.PP
This tool is useful for:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Periodically refreshing music library data in audiocontrol
.IP \(bu 2
Verifying music server connectivity and library availability
.IP \(bu 2
Monitoring library size and artist count
.IP \(bu 2
Debugging library loading issues
.IP \(bu 2
Integration with cron jobs or systemd timers
.RE
.SS Background Job Coordination
The tool implements bidirectional coordination with audiocontrol metadata updater background jobs to prevent database write conflicts and ensure smooth concurrent operation:
.TP
.B Scan tool waits for updaters:
When the scan tool starts, it checks for and waits for any running album or artist metadata updater jobs to complete before proceeding with the library scan.
.TP
.B Updaters wait for scan tool:
When metadata updaters (album or artist) attempt to write to the database, they automatically detect if a library scan is running. If detected, they wait up to 5 minutes for the scan to complete before writing their metadata.
.TP
.B Job registration:
The scan tool registers itself as an active library scan job (library_scan_mpd or library_scan_lms) during the refresh operation. Metadata updaters monitor for these jobs to coordinate their writes.
.TP
.B Timeout behavior (5 minutes):
If an updater or scan takes longer than expected, the coordination times out and operations proceed with a warning log to prevent indefinite blocking.
.TP
.B Error handling:
If coordination checks fail, operations proceed gracefully to ensure robustness. All coordination events are logged for troubleshooting.
.PP
This two-way coordination mechanism is transparent to the user and happens automatically without additional configuration or flags. It prevents "readonly database" errors that occur when multiple processes try to write concurrently.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-server-type " " \fITYPE\fR
Specify the music server type: \fBmpd\fR or \fBlms\fR (default: mpd)
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Specify the server hostname or IP address (default: localhost)
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Specify the server port. If not provided, defaults to:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
6600 for MPD
.IP \(bu 2
9000 for LMS
.RE
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-stats
Display library statistics after scanning (album count, artist count, track count, and artist listing)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan default local MPD library:
.B audiocontrol_scan_library
.TP
Scan MPD library on remote server:
.B audiocontrol_scan_library --host 192.168.1.100 --port 6600
.TP
Scan LMS library with statistics:
.B audiocontrol_scan_library --server-type lms --host 192.168.1.50 --port 9000 --stats
.TP
Scan with debug logging output:
.B RUST_LOG=debug audiocontrol_scan_library --stats
.TP
Scan LMS library and display statistics:
.B audiocontrol_scan_library -t lms -H 192.168.1.50 -s
.SH OUTPUT
When successful, the tool outputs:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Connection status to the music server
.IP \(bu 2
Album updater coordination status (if running)
.IP \(bu 2
Library scan progress and completion time
.IP \(bu 2
(With \fB--stats\fR) Detailed statistics including album count, artist count, track count, and a list of up to 20 artists
.RE
.PP
Example output when album and artist updaters are running:
.RS
.B [INFO] Connecting to MPD server at localhost:6600
.B [INFO] Album updater job is running. Allowing database writes to complete...
.B [INFO] Job progress: Processing 2543 albums
.B [INFO] Album updater progress: Processed 1250/2543 albums
.B [INFO] Album updater job completed. Proceeding with library scan.
.B [INFO] Artist updater job is running. Allowing database writes to complete...
.B [INFO] Job progress: Fetching metadata for 1205 artists
.B [INFO] Artist updater progress: Processed 600/1205 artists
.B [INFO] Artist updater job completed. Proceeding with library scan.
.B [INFO] Scanning MPD library...
.B [INFO] Library scan completed in 12.34s
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Control logging verbosity. Set to \fBdebug\fR for detailed output, or \fBinfo\fR (default) for standard output
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (connection failure, invalid server type, etc.)
.SH INTEGRATION EXAMPLES
.TP
Refresh library hourly via cron:
.B 0 * * * * /usr/bin/audiocontrol_scan_library --server-type mpd --stats > /var/log/audiocontrol_scan.log 2>&1
.TP
Refresh library via systemd timer (one-shot service):
.nf
[Unit]
Description=AudioControl Library Scan
After=network-online.target

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ExecStart=/usr/bin/audiocontrol_scan_library --server-type mpd --stats
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal
.fi
.TP
Use with remote LMS server:
.B audiocontrol_scan_library --server-type lms --host music.example.com --port 9000 --stats
.SH CONFIGURATION
The tool does not require a configuration file. It connects directly to the specified music server using the provided hostname and port options.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR audiocontrol (1),
.BR audiocontrol_lms_client (1)
.SH NOTES
The library scan is a blocking operation. For large libraries, the scan may take several minutes to complete. Consider running this tool during off-peak hours or as a background job.
.PP
If the album updater or artist updater is running, the tool will automatically wait for them to complete (up to 5 minutes each). This is normal behavior and ensures consistency between library scans and metadata updates.
